## Slide 6 — A Practical Enterprise Rollout

**Headline**
Build around the coding tools already in place.

**Body copy**
Most enterprises already have the starting point: AI-assisted coding plus light automated code review. Useful, but incomplete. The next step is to add the upstream and downstream discipline that turns coding speed into delivery speed.

**Chevron 1 — Step 1: Product and quality tool adoption**
**Add now**

* Define features in smaller, testable slices
* Write structured acceptance criteria
* Use one shared format linking features to expected behavior

**Result**
Code generation starts from clearer functional goals.

**Chevron 2 — Step 2: Automated TDD and feedback loops**
**Add next**

* Generate implementation against defined behavior
* Run tests automatically on each PR iteration
* Feed failed tests back into the PR until the behavior is complete

**Result**
The PR becomes a live loop of generation, testing, feedback, and correction.

**Chevron 3 — Step 3: Release, security, and policy automation**
**Layer in**

* Add security and policy checks into the same PR loop
* Use flags and staged rollout to ship smaller changes safely
* Route production failures and regressions back into the backlog and test suite

**Result**
The system gets faster without losing control. Small changes move from spec to code to test to release with tighter governance built in.

**Visual guidance**
Three large left-to-right chevrons.
Each chevron shows only: **actions** and **result**.

**Speaker note / emphasis line**
**This is not a rip-and-replace transformation. It is a practical build-out around the AI coding layer companies already have.**

