## Slide 7 — Conclusion

**Headline**
The future is not point AI adoption. It is one connected delivery process.

**Conclusion copy**
Most companies started by adding AI to coding. That was the obvious first move. The bigger opportunity is to connect upstream product definition with downstream testing, review, release, and feedback.

The winners will not just write code faster. They will define features more clearly, validate changes earlier, release in smaller increments, and learn faster from production.

**Closing takeaway**
**AI-native delivery happens when product definition, code generation, testing, and release operate as one system instead of separate handoffs.**

